    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan across **4 files** and **8 precise insertion points**:\n\n---\n\n## What's Being Added\n\nA `POST /api/rename` endpoint and `ollama rename SOURCE DESTINATION` CLI command that atomically renames a model: copy the manifest to the new name, then delete the old manifest and any orphaned layer blobs.\n\n---\n\n## 8 Steps\n\n### `api/types.go` â€” Step 1\nAppend `RenameRequest` after `CopyRequest` (line 765):\n```go\n// RenameRequest is the request passed to [Client.Rename].\ntype RenameRequest struct {\n    Source      string `json:\"source\"`\n    Destination string `json:\"destination\"`\n}\n```\n\n### `api/client.go` â€” Step 2\nAppend `Client.Rename()` after `Copy()` (line 387), calling `c.do(ctx, http.MethodPost, \"/api/rename\", req, nil)`.\n\n### `server/routes.go` â€” Step 3\nAppend `Server.RenameHandler()` after `CopyHandler` (line 1483). The handler:\n- Binds JSON, validates non-empty fields â†’ 400\n- Validates names with `model.ParseName()` / `.IsValid()` â†’ 400 with `errtypes.InvalidModelNameErrMsg`\n- Checks destination doesn't exist via `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` â†’ **409 Conflict** if found\n- Calls `CopyModel(src, dst)` â†’ 404 on `os.ErrNotExist`\n- Calls `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` â†’ `m.Remove()` â†’ `m.RemoveLayers()` to delete source\n- Returns `{\"status\":\"success\"}` on 200\n\nAll required packages (`errtypes`, `manifest`, `model`, `os`, `errors`, `fmt`, `io`, `gin`) are **already imported** â€” no import changes needed.\n\n### `server/routes.go` â€” Step 4\nAdd `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)` right after `r.POST(\"/api/copy\", ...)` (line 1698).\n\n### `cmd/cmd.go` â€” Step 5\nAppend `RenameHandler` func after `CopyHandler` (line 1350), printing `Renamed \"X\" to \"Y\"`.\n\n### `cmd/cmd.go` â€” Step 6\nAdd `renameCmd` cobra definition after `copyCmd` (line 2263) with `Use: \"rename SOURCE DESTINATION\"`, `cobra.ExactArgs(2)`.\n\n### `cmd/cmd.go` â€” Step 7\nAdd `renameCmd` to the env-docs loop after `copyCmd` (line 2298) so `OLLAMA_HOST` appears in `--help`.\n\n### `cmd/cmd.go` â€” Step 8\nAdd `renameCmd` to `rootCmd.AddCommand()` after `copyCmd` (line 2345).",
